This paper is about machine reading comprehension, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The paper proposes a new approach to integrating word and character embeddings to improve word representations, which is a common problem in NLP. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which is focused on NLP and speech processing. 

The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG and cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves attention mechanisms, which are also used in neural networks for various tasks such as image recognition and natural language processing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on various public benchmarks, which is a common practice in information retrieval (cs.IR).
